/*
:name: latch_active_low
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: latch_active_low.llow8
:pyrope_top: llow8
*/

// LIVE equiv test (promoted 2026-07-20, todo/livehd/2f-latch). A
// transparent-LOW latch: Q follows D while the gate is 0 and holds while it is
// 1 — the master half of every master/slave pair and the enable latch of every
// ICG. lgcheck's bounded miter DISCRIMINATES enable polarity (a port-matched
// polarity flip refutes — see lhd/tests/lec_latch_polarity_test.sh), so this
// PROVEN is meaningful, not vacuous.
//
// Today polarity is NOT carried by the Latch cell's `posclk` pin on the
// Pyrope/slang path — it is baked into the enable cone (`enable = !clk`), and
// `posclk` is only ever written by the yosys $dlatch importer. 2f-latch M2 makes
// `posclk` authoritative and cross-checks it against the enable cone; a
// disagreement between the two is the "posclk double-negation" miscompile that a
// symmetric before/after gate cannot see (hence the cross-model gating rule).
// This pair is the regression guard for that change.
pub mod llow8(clk:bool, d:u8) -> (q:u8@[0]) {
  reg l:u8:[latch=true]
  if !clk {
    l = d
  }
  q = l
}
